#BabyNames %>%group_by( First ) %>% summarise( votesReceived=n() )

don’t need to quote First. Dataset is wrong.

#Tmp <- group_by(BabyNames, year, sex ) %>% summarise( Tmp, totalBirths=sum(count))

You cannot call Tmp within the statement.

#Tmp <- group_by(BabyNames, year, sex)summarise( BabyNames, totalBirths=sum(count) )

There’s no link between the two verbs.

7.11 a) sex, count (total number of patients with that sex), meanAge (average age of patients of that sex)

  1. diagnosis, count (total number of patients with that diagnosis), meanAge (average age of patients of that diagnosis)

  2. sex, diagnosis, count (total number of patients with that sex and that diagnosis), meanAge (average age of patients of that sex and that diagnosis)

  3. age, diagnosis, count (total number of patients with that age and that diagnosis), meanAge (average age of patients of that age and that diagnosis)

  4. age, count (total number of patients at that age), meanAge (should be the age)
